comments: Crowder (PHX) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Shamet (PHX) lands short of Middleton (MIL) and would avoid Middleton's right leg if he didn't extend it forward to initiate the marginal contact during the follow-through.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) and Ayton (PHX) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Payne (PHX) moves forward toward Antetokounmpo (MIL) and marginal contact occurs with Antetokounmpo's front prior to and during his passing attempt.
Ayton (PHX) braces for the impending body contact with Antetokounmpo (MIL) and absorbs it as it occurs.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) goes to, not through, Ayton's (PHX) space and marginal contact occurs in the lane.
Ayton (PHX) initiates contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) right arm and side during his upward shooting motion.
Ayton (PHX) firms up in his screening position in Middleton's (MIL) path and does not deliver the contact as the defensive switch takes place.
Middleton (MIL) is already in Ayton's (PHX) path and absorbs the body contact that occurs as Ayton cuts toward the lane.
Middleton (MIL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Ayton (PHX) as simultaneous incidental contact occurs.
Crowder (PHX) turns into Middleton's (MIL) path and initiates body contact during the drive. The contact occurs prior to Middleton's off-arm moving toward Crowder thereafter.
Crowder (PHX) grasps and then quickly releases Allen's (MIL) left arm as he sets the screen.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Allen's (MIL) path and absorbs the contact.
Allen (MIL) intentionally kicks the ball.
Crowder (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Allen's (MIL) path and absorbs the marginal side-to-side contact.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) initiates contact across Ayton's (PHX) right arm during his upward shooting motion.
Portis (MIL) engages with Bridges (PHX) during the box-out and disengages as marginal contact occurs during rebounding.
Holiday (MIL) brings his off-arm toward Payne (PHX) and marginal contact occurs with Payne's left arm in the post.
Bridges (PHX) is retreating alongside Middleton's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs to Middleton's upper half during the drive.
Ayton (PHX) firms up in his screening position in Allen's (MIL) path and absorbs the contact.
Wigginton (MIL) legally contests Bridges' (PHX) jump shot attempt.
